00:13:37,890 --> 00:13:38,390
- Yeah.

260
00:13:38,390 --> 00:13:41,390
- Auntie Helen and Chacha
Victor were friends of my dad's.

261
00:13:41,390 --> 00:13:43,210
They were the couple
that I imagined

262
00:13:43,210 --> 00:13:46,170
my dad and Victoria were.

263
00:13:46,170 --> 00:13:48,410
How did Victor get to Harlem?

264
00:13:48,410 --> 00:13:52,362
And how did he and Helen meet?

265
00:13:52,362 --> 00:13:56,130
- He was a tender on
the British ships.

266
00:13:56,130 --> 00:13:59,730
He had to shovel coal
to run the engines.

267
00:13:59,730 --> 00:14:02,770
The ship landed in
Baltimore, and his friend

268
00:14:02,770 --> 00:14:04,770
told him to come with
him, that they were

269
00:14:04,770 --> 00:14:06,930
going to go see some people.

270
00:14:06,930 --> 00:14:10,450
But as the night wore on,
he says, well, I'm staying.

271
00:14:10,450 --> 00:14:11,470
You have no choice.

272
00:14:11,470 --> 00:14:12,930
You have to go with me.

273
00:14:12,930 --> 00:14:16,390
And they took a bus and
landed up in New York.

274
00:14:16,390 --> 00:14:19,168
[INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC]

275
00:14:19,168 --> 00:14:22,410

276
00:14:22,410 --> 00:14:25,930
Now there was a lady,
she was a Black lady.

277
00:14:25,930 --> 00:14:29,970
He stayed in her rooming house,
and there were other Indians

278
00:14:29,970 --> 00:14:30,510
there.

279
00:14:30,510 --> 00:14:33,360
[INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC]

280
00:14:33,360 --> 00:14:36,210

281
00:14:36,210 --> 00:14:40,210
My mother used to take
the train with my sisters.

282
00:14:40,210 --> 00:14:43,750
My future husband, he
would wait for my mother,

283
00:14:43,750 --> 00:14:46,150
and he would give her his seat.

284
00:14:46,150 --> 00:14:48,580
And then, my mother
invited him to the house.

285
00:14:48,580 --> 00:14:52,110

286
00:14:52,110 --> 00:14:54,790
I said, I guess he's
interested in my sister.

287
00:14:54,790 --> 00:14:56,210
She said, you can have him.

288
00:14:56,210 --> 00:14:57,850
I said, I don't want him.

289
00:14:57,850 --> 00:14:59,754
- [LAUGHING]

290
00:14:59,754 --> 00:15:01,320
- You had a boyfriend already?

291
00:15:01,320 --> 00:15:03,370
- No, I had no boyfriend.

292
00:15:03,370 --> 00:15:08,430
I worked as a nurse, and I
didn't want to be a housewife.

293
00:15:08,430 --> 00:15:11,330
He came back just
before Christmas.

294
00:15:11,330 --> 00:15:14,830

295
00:15:14,830 --> 00:15:18,750
He proposed to me, and
I was flabbergasted.

296
00:15:18,750 --> 00:15:21,750
And I said, oh my goodness.

297
00:15:21,750 --> 00:15:24,230
We decided we would get married.

298
00:15:24,230 --> 00:15:26,030
And I said to my
mother, you don't

299
00:15:26,030 --> 00:15:28,190
have to worry about the gown.

300
00:15:28,190 --> 00:15:31,150
We're not going to be married
in the Catholic Church.

301
00:15:31,150 --> 00:15:32,110
No pork.

302
00:15:32,110 --> 00:15:34,070
That's what I told my mother.

303
00:15:34,070 --> 00:15:37,990
That's when I was introduced
into the Indian community.

304
00:15:37,990 --> 00:15:42,758

305
00:15:42,758 --> 00:15:44,390
- Well, it was great seeing you.

306
00:15:44,390 --> 00:15:45,310
- Good to see you.

307
00:15:45,310 --> 00:15:45,990
Good to see you.

308
00:15:45,990 --> 00:15:46,860
Welcome, welcome.

309
00:15:46,860 --> 00:15:48,010
- Come on in.

310
00:15:48,010 --> 00:15:50,950
- [INAUDIBLE] and Ruth Ali ran
a restaurant together in Harlem,

311
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:53,250
not long after my dad and
Victoria opened the Bengali

312
00:15:53,250 --> 00:15:55,610
Garden in Times Square.

313
00:15:55,610 --> 00:15:59,330
I had heard about how Malcolm
X's circle used to eat there.

314
00:15:59,330 --> 00:16:02,220
This place became like a
fixture in the neighborhood.

315
00:16:02,220 --> 00:16:03,650
- How are you?

316
00:16:03,650 --> 00:16:04,290
How are you?

317
00:16:04,290 --> 00:16:04,790
- I'm good.

318
00:16:04,790 --> 00:16:07,070
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

319
00:16:07,070 --> 00:16:08,070
- --take your shoes off?

320
00:16:08,070 --> 00:16:08,570
- No.

321
00:16:08,570 --> 00:16:09,130
- No.

322
00:16:09,130 --> 00:16:10,430
[CHATTER]

323
00:16:10,430 --> 00:16:12,238

324
00:16:12,238 --> 00:16:14,170
- Come on and have a seat.

325
00:16:14,170 --> 00:16:18,290
There's just no great
order of any kind.

326
00:16:18,290 --> 00:16:23,390
- You know, it's funny, because
when we started this project,

327
00:16:23,390 --> 00:16:25,880
I never had any
pictures of my dad.

328
00:16:25,880 --> 00:16:28,070
I only knew him as an old man.

329
00:16:28,070 --> 00:16:30,390
- I remember that
picture so well.

330
00:16:30,390 --> 00:16:33,850
She was crying, and he was
taking care of a customer.

331
00:16:33,850 --> 00:16:36,480
And he'd just picked her up,
and then she stopped crying.

332
00:16:36,480 --> 00:16:38,160
- I think I was
about three months--

333
00:16:38,160 --> 00:16:38,910
- Yeah, something.

334
00:16:38,910 --> 00:16:40,493
- --three months
old, four months old.

335
00:16:40,493 --> 00:16:42,330
- And I was sitting in
the window like this.

336
00:16:42,330 --> 00:16:44,630
And he was passing with
a priest, and he was--

337
00:16:44,630 --> 00:16:46,070
I said, wow.

338
00:16:46,070 --> 00:16:47,690
I'm going to get
that guy right there.

339
00:16:47,690 --> 00:16:49,107
I'm going to get
that guy one day.

340
00:16:49,107 --> 00:16:50,030
Just like that.

341
00:16:50,030 --> 00:16:51,670
So I watched where he was going.

342
00:16:51,670 --> 00:16:56,550
It was this Indian restaurant
between 134th and 135th Street.

343
00:16:56,550 --> 00:17:00,000
He gave me the phone number
on the back of a matchbox.

344
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:02,430
- Did you notice he had a
strong accent, or was he--

345
00:17:02,430 --> 00:17:03,610
- Yeah, I didn't care.

346
00:17:03,610 --> 00:17:05,250
I was going for the good one.

347
00:17:05,250 --> 00:17:06,069
[LAUGHTER]

348
00:17:06,069 --> 00:17:07,559
I didn't care where he was from.

349
00:17:07,559 --> 00:17:09,253
[LAUGHS]

350
00:17:09,253 --> 00:17:12,061
[INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC]

351
00:17:12,061 --> 00:17:13,470

352
00:17:13,470 --> 00:17:16,710
He was a foreigner and
knowing in my heart

353
00:17:16,710 --> 00:17:20,109
that my family would
not accept him.

354
00:17:20,109 --> 00:17:24,329
I wasn't in South Carolina,
and I wasn't being watched.

355
00:17:24,329 --> 00:17:26,140
I felt a freedom.

356
00:17:26,140 --> 00:17:28,925
[INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC]

357
00:17:28,925 --> 00:17:32,830

358
00:17:32,830 --> 00:17:35,670
He opened the
restaurant in 1958.

359
00:17:35,670 --> 00:17:37,860
And shortly after
that, he got married.

360
00:17:37,860 --> 00:17:46,330

361
00:17:46,330 --> 00:17:49,650
He lived to get
up and go to work.

362
00:17:49,650 --> 00:17:51,130
He loved it.

363
00:17:51,130 --> 00:17:53,170
That was him in the kitchen.

364
00:17:53,170 --> 00:17:55,990
There was a counter in
the front, very American.

365
00:17:55,990 --> 00:17:58,750
There was four of us--
my brother, my mother.

366
00:17:58,750 --> 00:18:01,070
We worked-- chop
up, peel carrots.

367
00:18:01,070 --> 00:18:06,010
I'd stand on the soda crate
and watch him butcher the lamb,

368
00:18:06,010 --> 00:18:08,270
or the beef, or the
chicken and cut it up.

369
00:18:08,270 --> 00:18:11,310
And I had chicken curry just
about every day of my life,

370
00:18:11,310 --> 00:18:12,970
as far as I can recall.

371
00:18:12,970 --> 00:18:15,050
She would cook on Friday nights.

372
00:18:15,050 --> 00:18:17,777
We'd have our Southern
food on Friday nights

373
00:18:17,777 --> 00:18:18,610
up in the apartment.

374
00:18:18,610 --> 00:18:19,550
- But he liked it.

375
00:18:19,550 --> 00:18:20,070
He liked it.

376
00:18:20,070 --> 00:18:23,770
- We had our birthday
parties there.

377
00:18:23,770 --> 00:18:25,750
Miles Davis used to come in.

378
00:18:25,750 --> 00:18:27,430
I used to serve
him all the time.

379
00:18:27,430 --> 00:18:29,670
I remember Cicely
Tyson sitting there.

380
00:18:29,670 --> 00:18:31,300
- Morgan Freeman came.

381
00:18:31,300 --> 00:18:34,180
- Mark Breland, a boxer;
Kareem Abdul-Jabbar.

382
00:18:34,180 --> 00:18:37,450
[INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC]

383
00:18:37,450 --> 00:18:45,310

384
00:18:45,310 --> 00:18:47,410
My father passed away in 1982.

385
00:18:47,410 --> 00:18:50,190
She ran it for another
15 years without him.

386
00:18:50,190 --> 00:18:52,090
This little black woman
from Pawleys Island,

387
00:18:52,090 --> 00:18:53,690
South Carolina, you know what?

388
00:18:53,690 --> 00:18:55,570
That's why she went after him.

389
00:18:55,570 --> 00:18:58,230
Because she had to carry
on the legacy of running

390
00:18:58,230 --> 00:19:01,370
this Indian restaurant
17 years after he died.

391
00:19:01,370 --> 00:19:02,520
- Wow, he's no joke.

392
00:19:02,520 --> 00:19:05,095
- [LAUGHS]

393
